            "physical_description": "Costume design by Oliver Messel for The Queen in the Prologue of Marius Petipa's ballet <i>The Sleeping Beauty</i>, Sadler's Wells (now Royal) Ballet 1946 or later revision.  \nThe Queen is depicted in full frontal view, wearing an elaborate Baroque costume, with long, pointed bodice, encrusted with a lattice and stones, a stand-away ruff colar and full sleeves trimmed with gold; the panniered underskirt is pink, with a deep decorative border in dusky blue pink encrusted with gold scrolls; the topskirt falls into a panel at the front decorated with gold motifs and the sides are covered with a lattice set with gold 'stones'.  On the head is a triangular high headdress of gold ovals, trimmed with vermilion bows at the sides, and with plumes to the back.  From the back and over the topskirt falls an ermine-trimmed grey train.", 
